Recently, the robustness of the optical fingerprinting method has been the subject of scientific debate. Several studies have raised concerns regarding its sensitivity to data selection, medological assumptions, and statistical interpretation30,[?]. Conversely, other studies10,25 have defended its validity when applied with appropriate constraints and rigorous calibration. This ongoing discussion underscores the importance of transparent methodology and careful evaluation when applying the optical fingerprinting approach in climate analyses.Table 1
