As the anthropogenic impact started from 1920 onwards (Fig. 1b), and to assess the impact of such anthropogenic contribution to drought over this study region, we used the Standardized Precipitation Evapotranspiration Index (SPEI) as an indicator24. Fig. 3 illustrates the temporal evolution of SAT anomalies from the observation and multi-model mean and SPEI index values over an industrial period, highlighting a significant upward trend in both parameters. The SAT anomaly graph shows a clear and persistent increase, particularly pronounced in the industrial period. This increase in SAT anomaly (1.4 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
