These findings stress the need to address various human-driven factors, including GHG emissions, land use changes, and aerosols, to mitigate future SAT increases and their impact on drought conditions, fragile ecosystems, and food security in Africa. The dominance of anthropogenic forcings during the industrial era highlights the necessity for tailored reduction of anthropogenic activities over Africa.Table 2
